AN
AUTOMATIC
METHOD
FOR
FINDING
THE
GREATEST
OR
LEAST
VALUE
FUNCTION
THE
GREATEST
OR
LEAST
VALUE
OF
A
FUNCTION
OF
SEVERAL
VARIABLES
IS
TO
BE
FOUND
WHEN
THE
VARIABLES
ARE
RESTRICTED
TO
A
GIVEN
REGION
A
METHOD
IS
DEVELOPED
FOR
DEALING
WITH
THIS
PROBLEM
AND
IS
COMPARED
WITH
POSSIBLE
ALTERNATIVES
THE
METHOD
CAN
BE
USED
ON
A
DIGITAL
COMPUTER
AND
IS
INCORPORATED
IN
A
PROGRAM
FOR
MERCURY
